`comp_eq_left` states `comp g (id Y) = g`. `id_eq` states `id (Hom c Y) g = g`.
With these simplifications, the goal becomes `g = g`, which is true by reflexivity. The `simp` tactic handles this.
The `<;> try aesop` part is a common pattern to solve any trivial remaining goals after `simp`.

